The paper discusses machine learning and data analysis, which are typically associated with the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions optimization and random walks, which are topics in cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), respectively. The use of convex geometry suggests a connection to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), while the application of the algorithms to various fields suggests a connection to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
